    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-10-06T18:39:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-10-06T18:39:00-05:00" n="406"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d406">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">310.2/10–652: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The United States Representative at the United Nations</hi>
                        (<persName corresp="#p_AUSTINWR1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Austin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-10-06T18:39:00-05:00"
                            >October 6, 1952—6:39 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>326. Re Chinese representation. <persName corresp="#p_GROSSEA1">Gross</persName>
                    discussed with <persName corresp="#p_PADILLANERVOL1">Padilla Nervo</persName>,
                        <gloss target="#t_CHI1">Chi</gloss> representation question (<gloss
                        target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 127, Sept 23). <persName
                        corresp="#p_PADILLANERVOL1">Padilla</persName> strongly inclines to view
                    question cannot properly be raised by point of order and would like our
                    comments. He would be prepared to rule out of order <gloss target="#t_Sov1"
                        >Sov</gloss> attempt to raise <gloss target="#t_CHI1">Chi</gloss>
                    representation question at outset <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> and if
                    challenge is made, to call for <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> vote at once
                    without discussion on the challenge to his ruling.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_GROSSEA1">Gross</persName> explored possible advantage of
                    disposing of matter on basis contemplated para 2 reftel.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss>’s views urgently requested.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_AUSTINWR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Austin</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
